  Physics: Sunlight enters a drop, refracts, reflects off the back surface
  (Fresnel in Glass), and refracts out. The wavelength-dependent IOR separates
  colors naturally. The exit angle peaks at ~42° from the anti-solar point,
  producing the rainbow arc. The BVH makes intersection with 10,000 drops
  efficient (O(log N) per ray).

  The test is renderRainbow() at factor=10 (480×270). You can run it to see the
